(75, 'bop02627', 'chasse', 'Boker', 'Boker + collection 2013', 'Scott McGhee is an American Bladesmith (ABS) who lives and works in Southeastern North Carolina. Scott learned the art of bladesmithing at Penland School of Crafts at the age of 17, and has worked at a coal fired forge on and off since 1981. In August of 2009, he built a gas fired forge and began his bladesmithing in earnest. He is currently on a quest to obtain ABS Master Certification and begin knife making full time. The Boker Plus Collection knife for 2013 is based on his famous Cottonmouth custom piece. The blade shape and silhouette is typical of McGhee''s designs. To guarantee the best cutting performance, the blade is made of 440C premium stainless steel with an attractive two-tone finish. The comfortably shaped handle is made of brown Micarta, and features artistic mosaic pins. The stainless steel handguard prevents slipping, and completes this heavy duty piece. Includes a premium brown leather sheath, collector''s box and certificate of authenticity. Strictly limited to just 999 pieces worldwide.', 'tactical2013.jpg', 'micarta brun', '440c', 'lame : 20 cm', 'nb2AWtozFqA', 179, NULL),
